                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d934">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to advise your
                    excellency to the end that you kindly transmit the information to the President
                    that, according to a telegram received this day at the legation, my august
                    sovereign on leaving the opera house in Paris last night, in company with his
                    excellency the President of the French Republic, was the object of an anarchist
                    attempt by means of an explosive bomb.</p>
                <p>I am glad, however, to add that Don Alfonso and Monsieur Loubet escaped unscathed
                    from the abominable attempt and were given an enthusiastic ovation by the people
                    of Paris.</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. Pastor.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
